sub_title: Senior Project Manager at Mott MacDonald the Netherlands
summary:
Tia den Hartog is a senior project manager with more than 10 years experiences managing multinational and multidisciplinary proejcts. It is her passion to work on projects in sustainability, renewable energy and societal impact. 

Specialties: communication, training, regional Development, programme development, project management, energy transition, environmental management, and natural disaster management.

The project is jointly implemented by Eastern African Land Administration Network (EALAN) and ITC, the Faculty of Geoinformation Science and Earth Observation of the University of Twente in the Netherlands. The project kicked off in January 2015 will be completed in January 14th 2020. 

With this project we work together with Kadaster, MDF and LDGI Kenya. 

EALAN Member Institutions:
1.	Bahir Dar University, Ethiopia
